[ 2026-03-05 16:45:41,064 ] 99 root - INFO - Search Results:[{'score': 0.8724059, 'chunk_id': 'cb9ced74-4c20-4be6-94fe-c025ca10a262_18', 'doc_id': 'cb9ced74-4c20-4be6-94fe-c025ca10a262', 'content': '## Faster Exit for Startups\n\nMinistry of Corporate Affairs has notified Startups as ‘fast track firms’ enabling them to wind up operations within 90 days vis-a-vis 180 days for other companies. An insolvency professional\n\nshall be appointed for the Startup, who shall be in charge of the\n\ncompany for liquidating its assets and paying its creditors within\n6 months of filing an application in this regard.\n\nMinistry of Corporate Affairs guidelines on winding up: scan this QR code.', 'language': None, 'chunk_index': 18}, {'score': 0.8043191, 'chunk_id': 'cb9ced74-4c20-4be6-94fe-c025ca10a262_6', 'doc_id': 'cb9ced74-4c20-4be6-94fe-c025ca10a262', 'content': '## Intellectual Property Rights (IPR)\n\nTo promote awareness and adoption of IPRs by Startups and facilitate them in protecting and commercialising the IPRs, Startup India provides access to high quality Intellectual Property services and resources, including:\n\nFast-tracking of Startup patent applications: The patent application of Startups is fast-tracked for examination and disposal. The process is much faster for recognised Startups.', 'language': None, 'chunk_index': 6}, {'score': 0.8016238, 'chunk_id': 'cb9ced74-4c20-4be6-94fe-c025ca10a262_7', 'doc_id': 'cb9ced74-4c20-4be6-94fe-c025ca10a262', 'content': '• Panel of facilitators to assist in IP applications - Facilitators are responsible for providing\ngeneral advisory on different IPRs, and information on protecting and promoting IPRs in\nother countries. Central Government bears the entire fees of the facilitators for\nany number of patents, trademark or designs, and Startups only bear the cost of the\nstatuary fees payable.\n\n• **Rebate on filing of application:** Startups are provided an 80% rebate in filing of patents vis-a-vis other companies bringing down the cost from INR 8,000 to INR 1,600. This helps them cut down on costs in their early years. 50% rebate is also provided in filing of Trademarks vis-a-vis other companies decreasing the cost from INR 10,000 to INR 5,000.', 'language': None, 'chunk_index': 7}, {'score': 0.8013081, 'chunk_id': 'cb9ced74-4c20-4be6-94fe-c025ca10a262_11', 'doc_id': 'cb9ced74-4c20-4be6-94fe-c025ca10a262', 'content': '*The image displays a stylized, orange line-art icon featuring three human figures. The figures are depicted from the chest up, wearing formal attire including collared shirts and neckties. The central figure is slightly taller and positioned behind the other two, creating a visual arrangement often associated with a team, a group of professionals, or a family unit. The icon is set against a plain white background.*\n\n[^2]: 4000+\n\nIPR\n\nFacilitators\n\nFor any queries please call us on 1800115565 or drop us an email at dipp-startups@nic.in\n\n---\n\nRelaxation in Public Procurement Norms\n\nGovernment of India has authorised its Ministries, Departments and Public Sector Undertakings to relax norms in all public procurements. Startups are entitled to avail exemption on:\n\nPrior Turnover', 'language': None, 'chunk_index': 11}, {'score': 0.798648, 'chunk_id': 'cb9ced74-4c20-4be6-94fe-c025ca10a262_22', 'doc_id': 'cb9ced74-4c20-4be6-94fe-c025ca10a262', 'content': '## Tax Exemption for 3 years\n\nThe recognised Startups that are granted an Inter-Ministerial Board Certificate are exempted from income-tax for a period of 3 consecutive years out of 7 years since incorporation.\n\nStartups incorporated on or after 1st April 2016 can apply for income tax exemption.', 'language': None, 'chunk_index': 22}]
