[ 2026-03-05 16:46:33,702 ] 99 root - INFO - Search Results:[{'score': 0.9078541, 'chunk_id': 'cb9ced74-4c20-4be6-94fe-c025ca10a262_23', 'doc_id': 'cb9ced74-4c20-4be6-94fe-c025ca10a262', 'content': '## Exemption for the purpose of clause (viib) of sub-section (2) of section 56 of the Act\n\n• A DPIIT recognized Startup is eligible for exemption from the provisions of section 56(2)(viib) of the Income Tax Act.\n\n• The Startup has to file a duly signed declaration in Form 2 to DPIIT {as per notification G.S.R. 127 (E)} to claim the exemption from the provisions of Section 56(2)(viib) of the Income Tax Act\n\nHave a Startup? Get recognised by scanning below QR code.', 'language': None, 'chunk_index': 23}, {'score': 0.8413472, 'chunk_id': 'cb9ced74-4c20-4be6-94fe-c025ca10a262_3', 'doc_id': 'cb9ced74-4c20-4be6-94fe-c025ca10a262', 'content': '## DPIIT-Recognised Startups are eligible for the following benefits:\n\nIntellectual Property Rights (IPR) benefits\n\nRelaxation in public procurements norms\n\nSelf-Certification under Labour & Environment laws\n\nFund of Funds for Startups (FFS)\n\nFaster exit for Startups\n\nDPIIT-Recognised Startups may apply to IMB for the following benefits:\n\nSection 80 IAC: Income Tax exemption for 3 out of 7 years', 'language': None, 'chunk_index': 3}, {'score': 0.84109604, 'chunk_id': 'cb9ced74-4c20-4be6-94fe-c025ca10a262_20', 'doc_id': 'cb9ced74-4c20-4be6-94fe-c025ca10a262', 'content': '## Tax Exemption\n\nStartups incorporated on or after 1 $ ^{st} $  April 2016 can apply for income tax exemption. The Inter-Ministerial Board validates the innovative nature of the business for granting Income Tax Benefits and is constituted by representatives from DPIIT, DBT, and DST.\n\nTo apply for tax benefits, scan this QR code.', 'language': None, 'chunk_index': 20}, {'score': 0.83834696, 'chunk_id': 'cb9ced74-4c20-4be6-94fe-c025ca10a262_22', 'doc_id': 'cb9ced74-4c20-4be6-94fe-c025ca10a262', 'content': '## Tax Exemption for 3 years\n\nThe recognised Startups that are granted an Inter-Ministerial Board Certificate are exempted from income-tax for a period of 3 consecutive years out of 7 years since incorporation.\n\nStartups incorporated on or after 1st April 2016 can apply for income tax exemption.', 'language': None, 'chunk_index': 22}, {'score': 0.83758116, 'chunk_id': 'cb9ced74-4c20-4be6-94fe-c025ca10a262_11', 'doc_id': 'cb9ced74-4c20-4be6-94fe-c025ca10a262', 'content': '*The image displays a stylized, orange line-art icon featuring three human figures. The figures are depicted from the chest up, wearing formal attire including collared shirts and neckties. The central figure is slightly taller and positioned behind the other two, creating a visual arrangement often associated with a team, a group of professionals, or a family unit. The icon is set against a plain white background.*\n\n[^2]: 4000+\n\nIPR\n\nFacilitators\n\nFor any queries please call us on 1800115565 or drop us an email at dipp-startups@nic.in\n\n---\n\nRelaxation in Public Procurement Norms\n\nGovernment of India has authorised its Ministries, Departments and Public Sector Undertakings to relax norms in all public procurements. Startups are entitled to avail exemption on:\n\nPrior Turnover', 'language': None, 'chunk_index': 11}]
