ormation on protecting and promoting IPRs in\nother countries. Central Government bears the entire fees of the facilitators for\nany number of patents, trademark or designs, and Startups only bear the cost of the\nstatuary fees payable.\n\n• **Rebate on filing of application:** Startups are provided an 80% rebate in filing of patents vis-a-vis other companies bringing down the cost from INR 8,000 to INR 1,600. This helps them cut down on costs in their early years. 50% rebate is also provided in filing of Trademarks vis-a-vis other companies decreasing the cost from INR 10,000 to INR 5,000.', 'language': None, 'chunk_index': 7}, {'score': 0.83379096, 'chunk_id': 'cb9ced74-4c20-4be6-94fe-c025ca10a262_73', 'doc_id': 'cb9ced74-4c20-4be6-94fe-c025ca10a262', 'content': 'It shows a tweet from "Startup India" discussing funding from Japanese entities. Below the feed is a thumbnail image of a handshake. The top of the image contains a navigation bar with links like "ABOUT", "FOR STATES", and "FOR STARTUPS".*', 'language': None, 'chunk_index': 73}, {'score': 0.83182096, 'chunk_id': 'cb9ced74-4c20-4be6-94fe-c025ca10a262_121', 'doc_id': 'cb9ced74-4c20-4be6-94fe-c025ca10a262', 'content': '## Seed\n\nProduct/Service\nlaunched in Market\n\nFund Sources: Angel Investors, Pitching Competitions, Collateral-Free Debt', 'language': None, 'chunk_index': 121}]
